Anonymous Sat 09 Jul 2022 16:27:08 No.49179052 Report
Quoted By: >>49179368 >>49179480 >>49180474 >>49180967
>>49178940
I like to go with the idea that anthros are less ambitious and creative than humans, something inherent that isn’t immediately obvious. That anthros are satisfied with what works now and don’t have the pressure that humans feel to make everything better, more efficient, more innovative. Humans create technology and societal structures, like say the internet or the corporate hierarchy, and anthros are happy to just go along with these things once they’re established. They use them, sure, but only after humans have paved the way, which means different species gravitate naturally to different fields and interests. Wolves and other pack animals get into the corporate sphere, rats are into banking, mice get into tech, etc etc.
